      <title>Today's local history makers: We want to hear who is making Black history near you</title>
      <author>Brittney Melton</author>
      <link>https://www.npr.org/2025/02/06/g-s1-46798/local-black-history-month-changemakers</link>
      <comments>https://text.npr.org/2025/02/06/g-s1-46798/local-black-history-month-changemakers</comments>
      <guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.npr.org/2025/02/06/g-s1-46798/local-black-history-month-changemakers</guid>
      <pubDate>Thu, 06 Feb 2025 18:05:13 +0000</pubDate>
      <description>&lt;div id="storytext" class="storytext storylocation linkLocation"&gt;       &lt;div id="resg-s1-46802" class="bucketwrap image large"&gt;             &lt;div     class="imagewrap has-source-dimensions"     data-crop-type=""     style="         --source-width: 5384;         --source-height: 3582;     " &gt;         &lt;picture&gt;             &lt;source srcset="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/5384x3582+0+0/resize/1100/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F10%2Ff2%2F3bd9931948e784b5f6bdfec713e5%2Fgettyimages-1224656386.jpg" class="img" type="image/webp" data-template="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/5384x3582+0+0/resize/{width}/quality/{quality}/format/{format}/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F10%2Ff2%2F3bd9931948e784b5f6bdfec713e5%2Fgettyimages-1224656386.jpg" data-format="webp" /&gt;             &lt;source srcset="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/5384x3582+0+0/resize/1100/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F10%2Ff2%2F3bd9931948e784b5f6bdfec713e5%2Fgettyimages-1224656386.jpg" class="img" type="image/jpeg" data-template="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/5384x3582+0+0/resize/{width}/quality/{quality}/format/{format}/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F10%2Ff2%2F3bd9931948e784b5f6bdfec713e5%2Fgettyimages-1224656386.jpg" data-format="jpeg" /&gt;             &lt;img src="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/5384x3582+0+0/resize/1100/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F10%2Ff2%2F3bd9931948e784b5f6bdfec713e5%2Fgettyimages-1224656386.jpg" class="img" alt="A woman waves a Pan-African flag next to the Washington Memorial in Washington, D.C." data-template="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/5384x3582+0+0/resize/{width}/quality/{quality}/format/{format}/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F10%2Ff2%2F3bd9931948e784b5f6bdfec713e5%2Fgettyimages-1224656386.jpg" data-format="jpeg" /&gt;         &lt;/picture&gt; &lt;/div&gt; &lt;div class="credit-caption"&gt;     &lt;div class="caption-wrap"&gt;         &lt;div class="caption" aria-label="Image caption"&gt;             &lt;p&gt;                 A woman waves a Pan-African flag next to the Washington Memorial in Washington, D.C.                 &lt;b class="credit" aria-label="Image credit"&gt;                                          Roberto Schmidt/AFP via Getty Images/AFP                                      &lt;/b&gt;                 &lt;b class="hide-caption"&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;             &lt;/p&gt;         &lt;/div&gt;               &lt;b class="toggle-caption"&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;     &lt;/div&gt;       &lt;/div&gt;    &lt;/div&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Martin Luther King, Jr., Rosa Parks and Frederick Douglass are just some of the iconic names heard during Black History Month. Those well-known changemakers shaped today's world. However, they are not the only ones. Black history happens every day and can happen right in your town. The &lt;em&gt;Up First &lt;/em&gt;newsletter team wants to hear about the people making an impact locally.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;p&gt;If you know someone making history in the Black community right now, please share it with us via the form below, and you could be featured in the &lt;em&gt;Up First&lt;/em&gt; newsletter on Feb. 23. You can also share a photo and upload your answers as a voice memo. &lt;strong&gt;Please submit responses by Feb. 14.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;       &lt;p&gt;See some of your responses — and get the news you need to start your day — by &lt;a href="https://www.npr.org/newsletter/news" target="_blank"&gt;&lt;u&gt;subscribing to our newsletter&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div id="resg-s1-46798-100" class="bucketwrap statichtml"&gt;             &lt;iframe src="https://npr.formstack.com/forms/local_black_history_month_stories" title="Formstack Form" width="100%" height="1200"&gt;&lt;/iframe&gt;    &lt;/div&gt;     &lt;!-- END ID="RESG-S1-46798-100" CLASS="BUCKETWRAP STATICHTML" --&gt;    &lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;Your submission will be governed by our general &lt;/em&gt;&lt;a href="https://www.npr.org/about-npr/179876898/terms-of-use" target="_blank"&gt;Terms of Use&lt;/a&gt;&lt;em&gt; and &lt;/em&gt;&lt;a href="https://www.npr.org/about-npr/179878450/privacy-policy" target="_blank"&gt;Privacy Policy&lt;/a&gt;&lt;em&gt;. As the Privacy Policy says, we want you to be aware that there may be circumstances in which the exemptions provided under law for journalistic activities or freedom of expression may override privacy rights you might otherwise have.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/div&gt;</description>
      <category>Up First Newsletter</category>
