png/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fe4%2F50%2F7e869e4f46d6b66ca94444df570c%2Fscreenshot-2025-02-05-at-5-56-28-am.png 900w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/1292x727+0+62/resize/1200/quality/85/format/png/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fe4%2F50%2F7e869e4f46d6b66ca94444df570c%2Fscreenshot-2025-02-05-at-5-56-28-am.png 1200w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/1292x727+0+62/resize/1600/quality/85/format/png/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fe4%2F50%2F7e869e4f46d6b66ca94444df570c%2Fscreenshot-2025-02-05-at-5-56-28-am.png 1600w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/1292x727+0+62/resize/1800/quality/85/format/png/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fe4%2F50%2F7e869e4f46d6b66ca94444df570c%2Fscreenshot-2025-02-05-at-5-56-28-am.png 1800w" data-template="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/1292x727+0+62/resize/{width}/quality/{quality}/format/{format}/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fe4%2F50%2F7e869e4f46d6b66ca94444df570c%2Fscreenshot-2025-02-05-at-5-56-28-am.png" sizes="(min-width: 1300px) 763px, (min-width: 1025px) calc(100vw - 496px), (min-width: 768px) calc(100vw - 171px), calc(100vw - 30px)" class="img" type="image/png" /&gt;             &lt;img src="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/1292x727+0+62/resize/1100/quality/50/format/png/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fe4%2F50%2F7e869e4f46d6b66ca94444df570c%2Fscreenshot-2025-02-05-at-5-56-28-am.png" data-template="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/1292x727+0+62/resize/{width}/quality/{quality}/format/{format}/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fe4%2F50%2F7e869e4f46d6b66ca94444df570c%2Fscreenshot-2025-02-05-at-5-56-28-am.png" class="img" alt="If you can&amp;#039;t stop shaking your knee, don&amp;#039;t try to stop yourself. &amp;quot;Embrace the fidget,&amp;quot; says Katy Bowman, a biomechanist and the author of the book Rethink Your Position. That spontaneous movement can be your body&amp;#039;s way of telling you it&amp;#039;s time to move." loading="lazy" /&gt;         &lt;/picture&gt; &lt;/div&gt; &lt;div class="credit-caption"&gt;     &lt;div class="caption-wrap"&gt;         &lt;div class="caption" aria-label="Image caption"&gt;             &lt;p&gt;                 If you can't stop shaking your knee, don't try to stop yourself. "Embrace the fidget," says Katy Bowman, a biomechanist and the author of the book &lt;em&gt;Rethink Your Position&lt;/em&gt;. That spontaneous movement can be your body's way of telling you it's time to move.                 &lt;b class="credit" aria-label="Image credit"&gt;                                          &lt;i&gt;Kiersten Essenpreis for NPR&lt;/i&gt;                                      &lt;/b&gt;                 &lt;b class="hide-caption"&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;             &lt;/p&gt;         &lt;/div&gt;               &lt;b class="toggle-caption"&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;     &lt;/div&gt;       &lt;/div&gt;    &lt;/div&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Science shows that fidgeting is good for your health. It increases blood flow to limbs, helps regulate blood sugar, and reduces mortality risk from prolonged sitting. It can also relieve stress and anxiety. Physical therapists and researchers &lt;a href="https://www.npr.org/2025/02/02/nx-s1-5273803/fidgeting-desk-your-body-may-be-trying-to-tell-you-something" target="_blank"&gt;explain why we fidget&lt;/a&gt; and provide office-friendly ways to satisfy the need for movement. &lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;ul class="edTag"&gt;&lt;li&gt;🖊️ Fidgeting is a sign you need a break from a stagnant posture. Listen to your body and mix things up. Try alternating between sitting, standing and moving.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;🖊️ Get ahead of fidgeting by taking a movement break. Try going for a five-minute walk every half-hour.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;🖊️ If you need more help with your sensory needs, you could try keeping some fidget toys at your desk.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;       &lt;h3 class="edTag"&gt;3 things to know before you go&lt;/h3&gt;   &lt;div id="resg-s1-46463" class="bucketwrap image large"&gt;             &lt;div     class="imagewrap has-source-dimensions"     data-crop-type=""     style="         --source-width: 5945;         --source-height: 3344;     " &gt;         &lt;picture&gt;             &lt;source srcset="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/5945x3344+0+309/resize/400/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fae%2F06%2Fc346a74a41708fa8132ff7102cff%2Fgettyimages-2196873708.jpg 400w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/5945x3344+0+309/resize/600/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fae%2F06%2Fc346a74a41708fa8132ff7102cff%2Fgettyimages-2196873708.jpg 600w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/5945x3344+0+309/resize/800/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fae%2F06%2Fc346a74a41708fa8132ff7102cff%2Fgettyimages-2196873708.jpg 800w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/5945x3344+0+309/resize/900/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fae%2F06%2Fc346a74a41708fa8132ff7102cff%2Fgettyimages-2196873708.jpg 900w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/5945x3344+0+309/resize/1200/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fae%2F06%2Fc346a74a41708fa8132ff7102cff%2Fgettyimages-2196873708.jpg 1200w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/5945x3344+0+309/resize/1600/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fae%2F06%2Fc346a74a41708fa8132ff7102cff%2Fgettyimages-2196873708.jpg 1600w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/5945x3344+0+309/resize/1800/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fae%2F06%2Fc346a74a41708fa8132ff7102cff%2Fgettyimages-2196873708.jpg 1800w" data-template="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/5945x3344+0+309/resize/{width}/quality/{quality}/format/{format}/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fae%2F06%2Fc346a74a41708fa8132ff7102cff%2Fgettyimages-2196873708.jpg" sizes="(min-width: 1300px) 763px, (min-width: 1025px) calc(100vw - 496px), (min-width: 768px) calc(100vw - 171px), calc(100vw - 30px)" class="img" type="image/webp" /&gt;             &lt;source srcset="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/5945x3344+0+309/resize/400/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fae%2F06%2Fc346a74a41708fa8132ff7102cff%2Fgettyimages-2196873708.jpg 400w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/5945x3344+0+309/resize/600/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fae%2F06%2Fc346a74a41708fa8132ff7102cff%2Fgettyimages-2196873708.jpg 600w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/5945x3344+0+309/resize/800/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fae%2F06%2Fc346a74a41708fa8132ff7102cff%2Fgettyimages-2196873708.jpg 800w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/5945x3344+0+309/resize/900/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fae%2F06%2Fc346a74a41708fa8132ff7102cff%2Fgettyimages-2196873708.jpg 900w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/5945x3344+0+309/resize/1200/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fae%2F06%2Fc346a74a41708fa8132ff7102cff%2Fgettyimages-2196873708.jpg 1200w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/5945x3344+0+309/resize/1600/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fae%2F06%2Fc346a74a41708fa8132ff7102cff%2Fgettyimages-2196873708.jpg 1600w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/5945x3344+0+309/resize/1800/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fae%2F06%2Fc346a74a41708fa8132ff7102cff%2Fgettyimages-2196873708.jpg 1800w" data-template="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/5945x3344+0+309/resize/{width}/quality/{quality}/format/{format}/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fae%2F06%2Fc346a74a41708fa8132ff7102cff%2Fgettyimages-2196873708.jpg" sizes="(min-width: 1300px) 763px, (min-width: 1025px) calc(100vw - 496px), (min-width: 768px) calc(100vw - 171px), calc(100vw - 30px)" class="img" type="image/jpeg" /&gt;             &lt;img src="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/5945x3344+0+309/resize/1100/quality/50/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fae%2F06%2Fc346a74a41708fa8132ff7102cff%2Fgettyimages-2196873708.jpg" data-template="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/5945x3344+0+309/resize/{width}/quality/{quality}/format/{format}/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fae%2F06%2Fc346a74a41708fa8132ff7102cff%2Fgettyimages-2196873708.jpg" class="img" alt="Billie Eilish performs onstage with Billie Joe Armstrong of Green Day during the FIREAID Benefit Concert for California Fire Relief at The Kia Forum on January 30, 2025 in Inglewood, California." loading="lazy" /&gt;         &lt;/picture&gt; &lt;/div&gt; &lt;div class="credit-caption"&gt;     &lt;div class="caption-wrap"&gt;         &lt;div class="caption" aria-label="Image caption"&gt;             &lt;p&gt;                 Billie Eilish performs onstage with Billie Joe Armstrong of Green Day during the FIREAID Benefit Concert for California Fire Relief at The Kia Forum on January 30, 2025 in Inglewood, California.                 &lt;b class="credit" aria-label="Image credit"&gt;                                          Scott Dudelson/Getty Images for FIREAID/Getty Images North America                                      &lt;/b&gt;                 &lt;b class="hide-caption"&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;             &lt;/p&gt;         &lt;/div&gt;               &lt;b class="toggle-caption"&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;     &lt;/div&gt;       &lt;/div&gt;    &lt;/div&gt;    &lt;ol class="edTag"&gt;&lt;li&gt;The FireAid benefit concert, which features artists such as Olivia Rodrigo and Dr. Dre, is projected to have &lt;a href="https://www.npr.org/2025/02/05/nx-s1-5286481/fireaid-concert-la-wildfire" target="_blank"&gt;raised over $100 million for&lt;/a&gt; Los Angeles wildfire relief.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;The 2025 Academy Awards are slated for March 2. To help prepare, &lt;em&gt;Pop Culture Happy Hour&lt;/em&gt; has launched a pop-up newsletter that will go through all 10 best picture nominees. Click &lt;a href="https://www.npr.org/newsletter/movie-club" target="_blank"&gt;here&lt;/a&gt; to sign up.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;An 8-foot-tall &lt;a href="https://www.kcur.org/arts-life/2025-01-14/a-giant-butt-appeared-on-the-nelson-atkins-snowy-lawn-this-cheeky-artist-is-behind-it" target="_blank"&gt;snow sculpture of a butt&lt;/a&gt; was displayed on the south lawn of the Nelson-Atkins Museum of Art over the weekend. It's the latest cold collaboration from former Kansas City Art Institute students. (via &lt;a href="https://www.kcur.org/" target="_blank"&gt;KCUR&lt;/a&gt;)&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ol&gt;   &lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;This newsletter was edited by &lt;/em&gt;&lt;a href="https://www.npr.org/people/859721331/suzanne-nuyen"target="_blank"   &gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;Suzanne Nuyen&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;em&gt;.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/div&gt;</description>
