575a5e16.jpg" sizes="(min-width: 1300px) 763px, (min-width: 1025px) calc(100vw - 496px), (min-width: 768px) calc(100vw - 171px), calc(100vw - 30px)" class="img" type="image/jpeg" /&gt;             &lt;img src="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/4000x2250+0+0/resize/1100/quality/50/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F5f%2F76%2F3c6dcb12429696ba6581a920395b%2F20241217-195751-edit-wide-b1025adb447e713bd34305affb2c1f14575a5e16.jpg" data-template="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/4000x2250+0+0/resize/{width}/quality/{quality}/format/{format}/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F5f%2F76%2F3c6dcb12429696ba6581a920395b%2F20241217-195751-edit-wide-b1025adb447e713bd34305affb2c1f14575a5e16.jpg" class="img" alt="A type of jelly fungi, nestled by a log in wintertime in Maryland&amp;#039;s Patuxent River State Park." loading="lazy" /&gt;         &lt;/picture&gt; &lt;/div&gt; &lt;div class="credit-caption"&gt;     &lt;div class="caption-wrap"&gt;         &lt;div class="caption" aria-label="Image caption"&gt;             &lt;p&gt;                 A type of jelly fungi, nestled by a log in wintertime in Maryland's Patuxent River State Park.                 &lt;b class="credit" aria-label="Image credit"&gt;                                          Duncan Coltharp                                      &lt;/b&gt;                 &lt;b class="hide-caption"&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;             &lt;/p&gt;         &lt;/div&gt;               &lt;b class="toggle-caption"&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;     &lt;/div&gt;       &lt;/div&gt;    &lt;/div&gt;    &lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;Short Wave&lt;/em&gt; co-host and reporter Emily Kwong went on one of the monthly night hikes offered by a group of naturalists in the D.C. metro area. &lt;/strong&gt;Mycologist Serenella Linares led the group through Patuxent River State Park in Maryland. Before starting the hike, Linares told them of "the nature magic" ahead of them: bioluminescence, the fluorescence of fungi and lichens, insects that fly in the night and more. &lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;ul class="edTag"&gt;&lt;li&gt;📷 &lt;strong&gt;See photos&lt;/strong&gt; from the &lt;a href="https://www.npr.org/2025/01/27/1227405347/nature-wildlife-moth-lichen-fungi" target="_blank"&gt;colorful nature walk hike&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;   &lt;h3 class="edTag"&gt;3 things to know before you go&lt;/h3&gt;   &lt;div id="resg-s1-45170" class="bucketwrap image large"&gt;             &lt;div     class="imagewrap has-source-dimensions"     data-crop-type=""     style="         --source-width: 3791;         --source-height: 2753;     " &gt;         &lt;picture&gt;             &lt;source srcset="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/3791x2753+0+0/resize/400/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F3c%2F64%2F6166b5fe4829a6d65aae50ca0f65%2Fap25016728311222.jpg 400w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/3791x2753+0+0/resize/600/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F3c%2F64%2F6166b5fe4829a6d65aae50ca0f65%2Fap25016728311222.jpg 600w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/3791x2753+0+0/resize/800/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F3c%2F64%2F6166b5fe4829a6d65aae50ca0f65%2Fap25016728311222.jpg 800w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/3791x2753+0+0/resize/900/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F3c%2F64%2F6166b5fe4829a6d65aae50ca0f65%2Fap25016728311222.jpg 900w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/3791x2753+0+0/resize/1200/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F3c%2F64%2F6166b5fe4829a6d65aae50ca0f65%2Fap25016728311222.jpg 1200w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/3791x2753+0+0/resize/1600/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F3c%2F64%2F6166b5fe4829a6d65aae50ca0f65%2Fap25016728311222.jpg 1600w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/3791x2753+0+0/resize/1800/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F3c%2F64%2F6166b5fe4829a6d65aae50ca0f65%2Fap25016728311222.jpg 1800w" data-template="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/3791x2753+0+0/resize/{width}/quality/{quality}/format/{format}/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F3c%2F64%2F6166b5fe4829a6d65aae50ca0f65%2Fap25016728311222.jpg" sizes="(min-width: 1300px) 763px, (min-width: 1025px) calc(100vw - 496px), (min-width: 768px) calc(100vw - 171px), calc(100vw - 30px)" class="img" type="image/webp" /&gt;             &lt;source srcset="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/3791x2753+0+0/resize/400/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F3c%2F64%2F6166b5fe4829a6d65aae50ca0f65%2Fap25016728311222.jpg 400w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/3791x2753+0+0/resize/600/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F3c%2F64%2F6166b5fe4829a6d65aae50ca0f65%2Fap25016728311222.jpg 600w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/3791x2753+0+0/resize/800/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F3c%2F64%2F6166b5fe4829a6d65aae50ca0f65%2Fap25016728311222.jpg 800w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/3791x2753+0+0/resize/900/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F3c%2F64%2F6166b5fe4829a6d65aae50ca0f65%2Fap25016728311222.jpg 900w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/3791x2753+0+0/resize/1200/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F3c%2F64%2F6166b5fe4829a6d65aae50ca0f65%2Fap25016728311222.jpg 1200w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/3791x2753+0+0/resize/1600/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F3c%2F64%2F6166b5fe4829a6d65aae50ca0f65%2Fap25016728311222.jpg 1600w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/3791x2753+0+0/resize/1800/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F3c%2F64%2F6166b5fe4829a6d65aae50ca0f65%2Fap25016728311222.jpg 1800w" data-template="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/3791x2753+0+0/resize/{width}/quality/{quality}/format/{format}/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F3c%2F64%2F6166b5fe4829a6d65aae50ca0f65%2Fap25016728311222.jpg" sizes="(min-width: 1300px) 763px, (min-width: 1025px) calc(100vw - 496px), (min-width: 768px) calc(100vw - 171px), calc(100vw - 30px)" class="img" type="image/jpeg" /&gt;             &lt;img src="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/3791x2753+0+0/resize/1100/quality/50/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F3c%2F64%2F6166b5fe4829a6d65aae50ca0f65%2Fap25016728311222.jpg" data-template="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/3791x2753+0+0/resize/{width}/quality/{quality}/format/{format}/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F3c%2F64%2F6166b5fe4829a6d65aae50ca0f65%2Fap25016728311222.jpg" class="img" alt="A costumer exits a Starbucks store in Oakland, Calif." loading="lazy" /&gt;         &lt;/picture&gt; &lt;/div&gt; &lt;div class="credit-caption"&gt;     &lt;div class="caption-wrap"&gt;         &lt;div class="caption" aria-label="Image caption"&gt;             &lt;p&gt;                 Starbucks is trying to stem the loss of customers by simplifying its menu, reintroducing ceramic mugs and making other changes to be more like a local coffee house.                 &lt;b class="credit" aria-label="Image credit"&gt;                                          Godofredo A. Vásquez/AP                                      &lt;/b&gt;                 &lt;b class="hide-caption"&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;             &lt;/p&gt;         &lt;/div&gt;               &lt;b class="toggle-caption"&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;     &lt;/div&gt;       &lt;/div&gt;    &lt;/div&gt;    &lt;ol class="edTag"&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;By late this year, Starbucks plans to cut around 30% of its food and drinks offerings &lt;/strong&gt;as part of the chain's plan to change its vibe and derive from the &lt;a href="https://www.npr.org/2025/01/28/nx-s1-5278430/starbucks-cuts-drinks-food-simpler-menu" target="_blank"&gt;loss of customers across the U.S.&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;More than 100 former spies and intelligence officers oppose a proposed casino&lt;/strong&gt; that could be built less than 20 miles outside of the nation's capital due to &lt;a href="https://www.npr.org/2025/01/28/nx-s1-5273673/casino-spies-tysons-corner-washington-dc" target="_blank"&gt;concerns of state secrets being jeopardized&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Yoko, the swell shark, hatched at the Shreveport Aquarium earlier this month in a habitat without any males&lt;/strong&gt;, launching a mystery. The team determined that the two female sharks in the tank had &lt;a href="https://www.npr.org/2025/01/28/nx-s1-5276997/shark-shreveport-aquarium-parthenogenesis" target="_blank"&gt;not been in contact with a male&lt;/a&gt; in over three years.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ol&gt;       &lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;This newsletter was edited by &lt;/em&gt;&lt;a href="https://www.npr.org/people/1155154221/majd-al-waheidi"target="_blank"   &gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;Majd Al-Waheidi&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;em&gt;.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/div&gt;</description>
