%2Fc3%2F7c%2F97f33aa544eebba20c349cd88947%2Fgettyimages-2195811992.jpg 600w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/5499x3666+0+0/resize/800/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fc3%2F7c%2F97f33aa544eebba20c349cd88947%2Fgettyimages-2195811992.jpg 800w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/5499x3666+0+0/resize/900/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fc3%2F7c%2F97f33aa544eebba20c349cd88947%2Fgettyimages-2195811992.jpg 900w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/5499x3666+0+0/resize/1200/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fc3%2F7c%2F97f33aa544eebba20c349cd88947%2Fgettyimages-2195811992.jpg 1200w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/5499x3666+0+0/resize/1600/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fc3%2F7c%2F97f33aa544eebba20c349cd88947%2Fgettyimages-2195811992.jpg 1600w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/5499x3666+0+0/resize/1800/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fc3%2F7c%2F97f33aa544eebba20c349cd88947%2Fgettyimages-2195811992.jpg 1800w" data-template="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/5499x3666+0+0/resize/{width}/quality/{quality}/format/{format}/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fc3%2F7c%2F97f33aa544eebba20c349cd88947%2Fgettyimages-2195811992.jpg" sizes="(min-width: 1300px) 763px, (min-width: 1025px) calc(100vw - 496px), (min-width: 768px) calc(100vw - 171px), calc(100vw - 30px)" class="img" type="image/jpeg" /&gt;             &lt;img src="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/5499x3666+0+0/resize/1100/quality/50/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fc3%2F7c%2F97f33aa544eebba20c349cd88947%2Fgettyimages-2195811992.jpg" data-template="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/5499x3666+0+0/resize/{width}/quality/{quality}/format/{format}/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fc3%2F7c%2F97f33aa544eebba20c349cd88947%2Fgettyimages-2195811992.jpg" class="img" alt="Hiroto Ogiwara of Japan competes in the Men&amp;#039;s Snowboard Big Air at the X Games in Aspen on January 24." loading="lazy" /&gt;         &lt;/picture&gt; &lt;/div&gt; &lt;div class="credit-caption"&gt;     &lt;div class="caption-wrap"&gt;         &lt;div class="caption" aria-label="Image caption"&gt;             &lt;p&gt;                 Hiroto Ogiwara of Japan competes in the Men's Snowboard Big Air at the X Games in Aspen on January 24.                 &lt;b class="credit" aria-label="Image credit"&gt;                                          Ezra Shaw/Getty Images                                      &lt;/b&gt;                 &lt;b class="hide-caption"&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;             &lt;/p&gt;         &lt;/div&gt;               &lt;b class="toggle-caption"&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;     &lt;/div&gt;       &lt;/div&gt;    &lt;/div&gt;    &lt;ol class="edTag"&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;For the first time in history, Japanese snowboarder Hiroto Ogiwara and Italian skier Miro Tabanelli&lt;/strong&gt; pulled off a 2340, a &lt;a href="https://www.npr.org/2025/01/26/nx-s1-5275434/snowboard-ski-2340-x-games" target="_blank"&gt;six-and-a-half-rotation maneuver&lt;/a&gt;, in competition at the X Games in Aspen, Colo.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;American tennis player Madison Keys won her first Grand Slam title&lt;/strong&gt; at the Australian Open on Saturday, defeating Belarusian tennis player Aryna Sabalenka. Keys was &lt;a href="https://www.npr.org/2025/01/25/nx-s1-5274661/madison-keys-tennis-winner-grand-slam-title-aryna-sabalenka" target="_blank"&gt;ranked No. 19 going into the final match&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;More than 80 days after Election Day, Republican Jefferson Griffin is challenging roughly 65,000 votes&lt;/strong&gt; in a fight for a state high court seat. The 4th U.S. Circuit Court of Appeals will &lt;a href="https://www.npr.org/2025/01/27/nx-s1-5269775/north-carolina-supreme-court-challenged-ballots" target="_blank"&gt;hear arguments for the case today&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ol&gt;       &lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;This newsletter was edited by &lt;/em&gt;&lt;a href="https://www.npr.org/people/1155154221/majd-al-waheidi"target="_blank"   &gt;&lt;em&gt;Majd Al-Waheidi.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/div&gt;</description>
